if my strategy is considered kosher, but I show and I don't tell. Because I think a lot of people,

00:38:35.639 --> 00:38:41.719
when people, it's hard to imagine what a better case would be like. You know, you could say I'm

00:38:41.879 --> 00:38:45.560
going to develop an app, and it's going to optimize workflows, and it's going to make

00:38:45.560 --> 00:38:49.879
decision-making faster. You know, those are all kind of great business-like things, but they don't

00:38:49.879 --> 00:38:55.879
really show any emotion, right? So, it's hard to compel to the person above you in the tree to do

00:38:55.879 --> 00:39:01.560
it. So, I've always loved the show-don't-tell mentality. You know, work within the confines

00:39:01.560 --> 00:39:07.719
you have. Like the Shiny app that we talked about years ago that was on a network drive.

00:39:07.719 --> 00:39:11.879
We said, you know what, it's making changes. It's making people's lives better. But there's

00:39:11.879 --> 00:39:17.239
a lot of stuff I know I'm missing, and I don't want to do it wrong. I don't want to be Shadow

